Complex: strong unconscious influence on individual behaviour

#Sigmund Freud
Development
- oral: <1y, mouth
- anal: 1-3y, bowel+bladder
- phallic: 3-6y, genitalia
- latency: until puberty, dormant
- genital: after puberty
Ego
- id: instinctual desires
- superego: critical and moralizing
- ego: reason, reality principle
Oedipus complex: son desiring mother and rivaling father

#Carl Jung
Electra complex: girl competing with mother over father
Anima: unconscious feminine part in man
- Eve: object of desire
- Helen: self-reliant
- Mary: paragon of virtue
- Sophia: fully equal
Animus: unconscious masculine part in woman
Psychological Types
- attitude: extrovert, introvert
- function: perceiving (sensation, intuition), judging (thinking, feeling)

#Alfred Adler
Inferiority complex

Myers–Briggs Type Indicator (MBTI): 16 personality types based on Jung
- introversion/extroversion
- sensing/intuition
- thinking/feeling
- judging/perceiving

#Transactional analysis
Ego states
- Parent: exteropsyche, nurturing / criticising
- Child: archaeopsyche, emotions, intimacy
- Adult: neopsyche
Transactions
- Complementary: both in same state, e.g. Adult<>Adult
- Crossed: in different states, e.g. Adult>Adult + Parent>Child

#Emotional blackmail
fear, obligation, guilt
- Punisher's threat: I will hurt you
- Self-punisher's threat: I will hurt myself
- Sufferer's threat: I did something for you
- Tantalizer's threat: I will do something for you

#Dark triad
Machiavellianism: manipulation, deception, indifference to morality
Narcissism:
Psychopathy:

#Manipulation
Vulnerability
- Immaturity: naive, careless
- Impulsivity: snap decisions
- Low self-esteem: self doubt
- Over-conscientiousness: self blaming
- Over-intellectualization
- Emotional dependency: submissive, lonely
- Narcissism: prone to flattery
- Greed
Techniques
- lying
- lying by omission
- denial
- rationalization: excuse
- minimization
- selective attention
- diversion
- evasion
- intimidation
- guilt trip
- shaming
- villifying the victim
- playing the victim
- seduction
- blaming: scapegoat
- feigning innocence
- feigning confusion
- anger
- bandwagon effect: peer pressure
- flattery: compliments
More
- gaslighting: undermining perception of reality
- brainwashing: reducing ability of critical thinking
- indoctrination
- good cop, bad cop: interrogation technique, punishment/reward

#Personality disorder
Eccentric
- Paranoid: irrational suspicion
- Schizoid: emotional detachment
- Schizotypal: distorted cognition, unusual beliefs
Erratic
- Narcissistic: need for admiration, lack of empathy
- Histrionic: attention seeking, exhibitionism
- Borderline: emotional outburst, unhealthy attachment
- Antisocial: lack of remorse, manipulative
Anxious
- Avoidant: extreme sensitivity
- Dependent: 
- Obsessive-compulsive: perfectionism, conformity to rules
Depressive
- Depressive
- Cyclothymia: bipolar
Other
- Passive–aggressive
- Self-defeating: masochistic
- Sadistic: cruel
- Psychopathy: lack of empathy and remorse
- Haltlose: unstable
- Immature: lack of personal responsibility
- Organic: post-traumatic

#Stress
- increased corticol and catecholamines
Fight-or-flight response: discharge of sympathetic nervous system

#Autonomic nervous system
Sympathetic: arousal
Parasympathetic: calming

#Mental disorder
Schizophrenia: episodes of psychosis, hallucinations, delusions
Post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD): after traumatic event (rape, war)
- increased catecholamines but decreased cortisol
Clinical depression / Dysthymia: low mood and low self-esteem
Bipolar disorder: periods of depression and mania
Insomnia: trouble sleeping
Obsessive–compulsive disorder (OCD): need to perform routines repeatedly
Anxiety / Phobia: significant fear
- Acrophobia: heights
- Aerophobia: flying
- Agoraphobia: open/crowded spaces
- Arachnophobia: spiders
- Astraphobia: thunder
- Claustrophobia: enclosed spaces
- Cynophobia: dogs
- Mysophobia: germs
- Ophidiophobia: snakes
- Trypanophobia: needles
- Trypophobia: holes

#Symptoms
Hallucination: perception in absence of stimulus
Delusion: false fixed belief not amenable to change
Emotional blunting: failure to express feelings
Psychosis: difficulty to recognize what is real

Trauma: serious distressing event

#Personality factors
Neuroticism / emotional stability
- Anxiousness / unconcerned
- Angry hostility / dispassionate
- Depressiveness / optimistic
- Self-consciousness / shameless
- Impulsivity / restrained
- Vulnerability / fearless
Open-mindedness / closed-minded
- Fantasy / concrete
- Aesthetics / disinterest
- Feelings / alexithymia
- Actions / predictable
- Ideas / closed-minded
- Values / dogmatic
Agreeableness / antagonism
- Trust / mistrust
- Straightforwardness / deception
- Altruism / exploitative
- Compliance / aggression
- Modesty / arrogance
- Tender-mindedness / tough-minded
Extraversion / introversion
- Warmth / coldness
- Gregariousness / withdrawal: company of others
- Assertiveness / submissiveness: control by others
- Activity / passivity
- Excitement seeking / lifeless
- Positive emotionality / anhedonia: experience of pleasure
Conscientiousness / disinhibition
- Competence / laxness
- Order / disorderly
- Dutifulness / irresponsibility
- Achievement striving / lackadaisical: effort
- Self-discipline / negligence
- Deliberation / rashness

#Flow model: skill vs challenge level
High skill:
- High challenge: Flow
- Medium challenge: Control
- Low challenge: Relaxation
Low skill:
- High challenge: Anxiety
- Medium challenge: Worry
- Low challenge: Apathy
Medium skill:
- High challenge: Arousal
- Low challenge: Boredom

#Milgram experiment: tested obedience to authority
- participants administered electric shocks despite their conscience

Ulysses contract: decision binding oneself in future
Rorschach test: psychological test, inkblots
Winner's curse: value overestimation in auction bids (desire to win)
